(794, 381, 1, '2023-03-22 03:44:39', 233, 'comment', '<r><p>OKX Chain, also referred to as OKC, is a blockchain that is built upon the Cosmos architecture and is fully compatible with the Ethereum Virtual Machine (EVM). As such, OKC boasts a dual nature, combining the features of both Cosmos and EVM.</p>\n\n<p>Notably, OKC supports Inter-Blockchain Communication (IBC), allowing for seamless asset transfers between OKC and other Cosmos-based chains. Additionally, as a fully EVM-compatible chain, OKC facilitates the migration of smart contracts from other EVM-based chains to its platform.</p>\n\n<p>Furthermore, our OKC mainnet is set to release the WebAssembly (Wasm) virtual machine. This feature has already been successfully launched on the OKC testnet and is open to developers for testing. With the introduction of Wasm, developers proficient in languages such as C++, Rust, and Go can author smart contracts on the OKC platform. We welcome the developer community to join us in exploring the possibilities of OKC.</p>\n\n<p>OKC Developer Documentation: <URL url=\"https://www.okx.com/okc/docs/dev/quick-start/overview.html\">https://www.okx.com/okc/docs/dev/quick-start/overview.html</URL></p></r>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '198.13.46.111', 0, 1, 0, 0),
(795, 382, 1, '2023-03-22 09:42:13', 38, 'comment', '<r><H2><s>## </s>Background</H2>\n<p>When you execute <C><s>`</s>make testnet<e>`</e></C> or <C><s>`</s>make mainnet<e>`</e></C> with okc code, you may encounter the following error:</p>\n<CODE><s>```</s><i>\n</i>ld: library not found for -llz4\n\nld: library not found for -lsnappy<i>\n</i><e>```</e></CODE>\n<p>These errors are usually found on MacOS.</p>\n\n<H2><s>## </s>Solution</H2>\n<LIST type=\"decimal\"><LI><s>1. </s><p>First make sure you have successfully executed <C><s>`</s>make rocksdb<e>`</e></C></p></LI>\n<LI><s>2. </s><p>For MacOS, execute the following command:</p>\n<CODE><s>```</s><i>\n</i>brew update\nbrew install snappy \n# or\nbrew install lz4<i>\n</i><e>```</e></CODE></LI>\n\n<LI><s>3. </s><p>Retry <C><s>`</s>make testnet<e>`</e></C> or <C><s>`</s>make mainnet<e>`</e></C>. Usually the problem is solved.</p></LI>\n<LI><s>4. </s><p>Try this if it is still not working, and retry <C><s>`</s>3<e>`</e></C>:</p>\n<CODE><s>```</s><i>\n</i>export LIBRARY_PATH=$LIBRARY_PATH:$(brew --prefix lz4)/lib/\nexport LIBRARY_PATH=$LIBRARY_PATH:$(brew --prefix snappy)/lib/<i>\n</i><e>```</e></CODE></LI>\n\n<LI><s>5. </s><p>In rare cases, you may encounter this error:</p>\n<CODE><s>```</s><i>\n</i>In file included from _cgo_export.c:4:\ndebugger.go:23:13: warning: unused function \'_duk_debugger_attach\' [-Wunused-function]\n# github.com/okex/exchain/cmd/exchaind\n/usr/local/go/pkg/tool/darwin_arm64/link: running clang failed: exit status 1\nld: warning: ignoring file /usr/local/lib/librocksdb.dylib, building for macOS-arm64 but attempting to link with file built for macOS-x86_64\nld: warning: ignoring file /usr/local/opt/snappy/lib//libsnappy.dylib, building for macOS-arm64 but attempting to link with file built for macOS-x86_64\nld: warning: ignoring file /usr/local/opt/lz4/lib//liblz4.dylib, building for macOS-arm64 but attempting to link with file built for macOS-x86_64\nUndefined symbols for architecture arm64:\n  \"_rocksdb_approximate_memory_usage_create\", referenced from:\n      __cgo_9c7e07974d9b_Cfunc_rocksdb_approximate_memory_usage_create in 000015.o\n     (maybe you meant: __cgo_9c7e07974d9b_Cfunc_rocksdb_approximate_memory_usage_create)\n  \"_rocksdb_approximate_memory_usage_destroy\", referenced from:\n      __cgo_9c7e07974d9b_Cfunc_rocksdb_approximate_memory_usage_destroy in 000015.o<i>\n</i><e>```</e></CODE></LI></LIST>\n\n<p>This means you are on a arm64 system but have the x86 libraries installed。it happens when you install the wrong version brew.  you need to reinstall the brew in the system terminal. then perform the above steps, but of course you need to uninstall the installed lz4 or snappy first.</p></r>', '2023-03-22 09:53:59', 38, NULL, NULL, '103.82.4.156', 0, 1, 0, 0);
